President Muhammadu Buhari has said that his Government is highly confident more than ever before on the Treasury and the Treasury Managers in ensuring Prudent and Transparent financial management of the Country. Speaking while closing a three days 2020 Management Retreat for Treasury Directors of Finance and Accounts and Directors of Internal Audit, the Accountant General of the Federation Ahmed Idiris, said the government is highly confident that the Nation Financial managers are ready to salvage the misfortune in the Treasury system of Nigeria. Ahmed Idiris explained that the retreat has availed them a high sense of opportunity to look at numerous challenges known and unknown and issues were discussed frankly while solutions were also proffered. The Retreat with a theme, ” Global Best Practices 21th Century Treasury Management “, saw all the nation financial managers coming together to create a solutions to the nation financial dwindling misfortune. The Accountant General of the Federation Ahmed Idiris explained that they have entered into a Memorandum of Understanding with the Nigeria Open University to start running a Business School at the University for the Nation financial managers. He said the aim is to allow the Treasury managers avail themselves with professional skills in managing the Country accounts. ” However, one cannot benefit from the new Open University Business School proposed creation if he is not ICT compliant, therefore you should do all you could to improve your Information Technology skills “. The Accountant general then formed a new team that would deploy Directors of Revenue with a term of Reference to develop a template for revenue generation, develop clear rules of engagement for Directors of revenue and set new rules.